10 (A) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ORGANIZE THE MARYLAND MEDICAL
11 RESERVE CORPS.
12 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE CORPS IS TO PROVIDE A STATEWIDE VOLUNTEER
13 NETWORK INTEGRATED INTO COMMUNITY EMERGENCY SYSTEMS TO FACILITATE A
14 COORDINATED APPROACH TO VOLUNTEER MANAGEMENT.
15 (C) THE CORPS SHALL INCLUDE CLINICAL AND NONCLINICAL PERSONNEL
16 CAPABLE OF ASSISTING DURING CRISES THAT STRAIN THE HEALTH CARE SYSTEM
17 OR PUBLIC HEALTH SYSTEM, INCLUDING PUBLIC HEALTH EMERGENCIES, DISEASE
18 OUTBREAKS, AND NATURAL DISASTERS.
